{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981775938,"sessionID":"ses_1cc7a7d0fffermSmuWmOnZbHoM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_57fMy7xd6uWnWVnMZu8quACN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Obsoleted `GO:7770028` `glycoprotein cargo receptor activity` and replaced it with `GO:0038024` `cargo receptor activity`.\n+\n+There were no direct annotations reported for this term in the annotation lookup, and I did not find ontology-internal usages that needed rewiring.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR `<NN>`.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Obsoleted `GO:7770028` `glycoprotein cargo receptor activity` as requested in issue `#31948`, with direct replacement to `GO:0038024` `cargo receptor activity`.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue rationale is that this term classifies cargo receptors by substrate type (`glycoprotein`) rather than by transport domain, which makes the term an error-prone classification axis.\n+- The requested replacement term is the broader parent `cargo receptor activity (GO:0038024)`.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+- Converted `GO:7770028` to an obsolete term in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+- Preserved the original definition provenance and prefixed the definition with `OBSOLETE.`\n+- Removed the asserted parentage from the obsolete term\n+- Added an obsoletion comment explaining the reason\n+- Updated `term_tracker_item` to point to issue `#31948`\n+- Added `is_obsolete: true`\n+- Added `replaced_by: GO:0038024`\n+\n+Checks performed:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed and intent was clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed before changes\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: verified the target term and replacement term in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: followed the obsoletion workflow\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: removed obsolete-term logical/structural axiom